Key Match Events: India beat Zimbabwe by ten wickets in the fourth T20I with openers Yashasvi Jaiswal and Shubman Gill taking them home in 15.2 overs.
Post-Match Reflections: Yashasvi Jaiswal, the Player of the Match for his outstanding knock of 93 runs off just 53 balls.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The final match of the series, now a dead rubber, will still be an opportunity for India to showcase their depth and for Zimbabwe to salvage some pride.
